        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="zQhQzCSvZs7QWjj12YHX-20" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h2&gt;Why Linux?&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Cloud is mainly linux, its faster, more secure, platform independent.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Best Operating System for Systems (where limitted User Interface is needed)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Who Uses Linux?&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Tech Companies&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Developers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Super Computers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Research Labs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Embeded systems&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Iot (Internet of Things basically all smart devices)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;What is Kali Linux?&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Used by Cyber Security for Ethical hacking.&amp;nbsp;Many ready to use tools out of the box that can be used for performance testing, penetration testing, etc&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="320" width="760" x="40" y="480" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="zQhQzCSvZs7QWjj12YHX-21" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;" value="&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Birth of C&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;The C programming language was introduced by Dennis Ritchie at Bell Labs in the early 1970s primarily to develop the Unix operating system&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;It was designed to address the limitations of existing languages like B and assembly language by providing a balance of low-level hardware access and high-level, portable programming features.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;This was basically an interface (intermediatory) between Assembly Level Language and High Level Languag&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;C Language is also portable. can run in any hardware. It became primary programming language to develop Operating System.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="160" width="760" x="40" y="860" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="zQhQzCSvZs7QWjj12YHX-24" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;fontSize=12;" value="&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Birth of UNIX&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;Development of the Unix operating system began in 1969 at AT&amp;amp;T Bell Labs by Ken Thompson and Dennis Ritchie.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The first edition (Unix 1st Edition) was released on November 3, 1971, accompanied by the first edition of the Unix Programmer&#39;s Manual&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="110" width="760" x="40" y="1120" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
